To clear the page before printing the text in a section, include
[code:16q9d8h7]@clear[/code:16q9d8h7]
in the section.

To automatically clear the page in every section, you can use a master section. Read more about those [url=http&#58;//docs&#46;textadventures&#46;co&#46;uk/squiffy/master&#46;html:16q9d8h7]here.[/url:16q9d8h7]

[code:16q9d8h7]&#91;&#91;&#93;&#93;&#58;
@clear[/code:16q9d8h7]

So you might end up with something like this:

[code:16q9d8h7]&#91;&#91;Page1&#93;&#93;&#58;
This is the first page&#46;

&#91;&#91;Option 1&#93;&#93;

&#91;&#91;Option 2&#93;&#93;


&#91;&#91;Option 1&#93;&#93;&#58;
This is the page for Option 1&#46;


&#91;&#91;Option 2&#93;&#93;&#58;
This is the page for Option 2&#46; 


&#91;&#91;&#93;&#93;&#58;
@clear[/code:16q9d8h7]

To format the text, you can use Markdown (see [url=http&#58;//daringfireball&#46;net/projects/markdown/syntax:16q9d8h7]this guide[/url:16q9d8h7]) and HTML.
